cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY

The paper discusses access control and trust computing in the context of the Internet of Things, which involves security and networking issues. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions existing work on access control models and systems, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses network attacks and cheating technologies, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of trust computing could also place the paper in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
